properties.Title: Snowfall Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Snowfall with total amounts of 15 to 25 cm is expected. A Pacific low moving eastward just south of Vancouver Island will bring very heavy precipitation to southern Vancouver Island on Monday. Heavy rain will switch over to heavy wet snow in the morning. Within about a 6 hour period snowfall accumulations may exceed 20 cm over higher elevations. The snow will end by late Monday afternoon as the low moves to the east. ### Rapidly accumulating snow will make travel difficult. Visibility may be suddenly reduced at times in heavy snow. Surfaces such as highways, roads, walkways and parking lots may become difficult to navigate due to accumulating snow. Weather in the mountains can change suddenly resulting in hazardous driving conditions. Road conditions are available at www.drivebc.ca. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to BCstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #BCStorm.
